animals.Name: Bella
animals.Description: Bella is a sweet, lop-eared rabbit, about three years old. She came to Triangle Rabbits from one of the local area shelters when she was pregnant with a litter of babies. Those babies are grown and have been adopted, and now Bella is ready to find her forever home. Bella likes chewing paper bags and also exploring inside them, and gets very excited when food comes out. She is shy and learning to like humans. She likes for people to ask before touching her so she does not get startled. Once she realizes pets are being offered, she likes to have her ears stroked and be rubbed on the back. She would love a home with a new friend for company. Currently fostering in the Raleigh-Durham area.

animals.Name: Honey
animals.Description: Meet Honey & Juniper! These two sisters are about 7 months old and must be adopted together. They may be small, but they need a lot of space to play and more importantly, to get away from each other when they want some alone time. They are currently living in a 10x11 bunny proofed room, but if they could talk, they would probably say they could use a little more square footage. They love to munch on hay all day long, but in the morning they circle like sharks for pellets. They also enjoy eating veggies twice a day. They are still pretty shy, but they will warm up to you if you give them time. They are also quite active and would prefer to run around than be pet. They make great bunny entertainment AKA bunny TV! Currently fostering in the Charlotte area.

animals.Name: Oreo
animals.Description: Meet Oreo! He was surrendered to a local shelter due to human allergies. He's a sweet, curious bunny who likes to explore his space and then flop out on the floor. Oreo enjoys almost all veggies, and he loves a bit of alfalfa as a treat. He does well with other small, gentle animals. Like most rabbits, he's not overly fond of being picked up, but he does enjoy a good nose rub.

animals.Name: Bentley
animals.Description: Are you looking for an excellent conversationalist? Bentley may be your perfect match! He loves to honk and talk, and is always happy to share his opinions. He is sweet and loves pets, destroying toys, and most of all, food! He can be protective of his food and his space, so a rabbit experienced home would be a great fit for him. Bentley enjoys having lots of free time and is not a fan of his enclosure. He loves to explore - that is the most fun! He is about a three years old, and is currently fostering in Raleigh-Durham, NC.

animals.Name: Maddie
animals.Description: We love big buns and we cannot lie! Meet our beautiful redhead Maddie. She is a Flemish giant mix and is about three years old. She is a shy lady and prefers to meet people in her own time. Once she gets to know you, she loves to be pet and will sit all day for rubs. Her favorite treat is banana (though, really, all treats are nice). She is good with her litter box, and enjoys re-arranging her hay to her liking (FYI, she says it goes in the front!). She is curious about the other bunnies sin her foster home, but seems happier in her space and doesn't venture too far. She is currently fostering in the Wilmington area.

animals.Name: Eeyore
animals.Description: Eeyore is about 7 months old and, while a bit shy, does enjoy a soft petting after dinner. He has an adventurous palate and the only thing so far he hasn't cared for is.... NOTHING! All salad is delicious! He would love a home with lots of freedom to run around and play. He is a sweet rabbit who likes remodeling sturdy cardboard boxes. He will contentedly do construction all day on them. When left alone too long he will also move all of his furniture around. He can be very curious and then does some firm nudging! He is not destructive and has excellent litter box habits. Currently fostering in the Wilmington area.

animals.Name: Snorlax
animals.Description: Transfer from shelter because has URI and would have been euthanized.

animals.Name: Hermey
animals.Description: Hermey was named after the elf who wanted to be a dentist in the classic Rudolph movie. He is very friendly and wants to be petted all day; he may even give you a kiss back! Hermey spends a lot of time running around and doing the Binky 500, especially through his favorite crinkle tunnel. He loves to boop his jingle ball toy with his nose and observe from the top of his cottage. Hermey also loves his fuzzy bed and will snuggle into it for a snooze. He's a great hay eater and has a big appetite. He is doing well learning the litter box and mostly keeps everything in the box now. He would be a great companion for someone who can give a lot of attention, and he may do well with a bunny friend! He is currently fostering in the Raleigh-Durham area.

animals.Name: Opal
animals.Description: Look who is ready for a home - it's Opal! This beautiful girl needed emergency hip surgery when she came to rescue in November 2022. She is healed and ready for a home of her own. Her hip will continue to solidify the false joint for several more months, but she doesn't need to wait until then to be adopted and we're so excited for her! Opal is very nosy and into everything. If she even *thinks* you have food in your hand she closes her eyes, opens her mouth, and goes in for the bite - hilarious! She like sto explore and is curious about everything, but when it comes down to it she loves a good head rub the most. Her mobility is great; she is still building up strength in her surgery leg. Opal is about 2 years old, spayed and vaccinated for RHDV2. She is currently fostering in the Raleigh-Durham, NC area.

animals.Name: Pebbles
animals.Description: Pebbles is a friendly girl who loves roaming around and exploring in and on top of boxes. She enjoys pets on her head, ears, and back after she's had her free time to roam. Peebles excitedly greets her foster family at her pen for breakfast and exercise time. We have yet to find greens or treats she doesn't like. Peebles has top notch bunstruction skills and especially loves chewing wooden and cardboard toys. You can find her keeping up with the latest in bunny decor trends as she rearranges her hideaway and chew toys in her pen. She is about 1.5 years old. Pebbles is currently fostering in the Raleigh-Durham area.

animals.Name: Georgia
animals.Description: Georgia is about three years old, spayed, and ready for a family of her own. She is a sweet girl who loves head pets. She gets along well with the cat in her foster home, so may enjoy a cat or bunny friend. She has a lot of fun with her toys, and regularly steals the cat lounger from her housemate. Georgia is a great timothy eater and loves her pellets and any fresh fruits or veggies. She does have an old hip injury. She is good with her litter box. She would do best in a gentle family that speaks rabbit. Georgia is currently fostering in the Raleigh-Durham area.

animals.Name: Goji
animals.Description: Goji is one spicy and salty girl! This aspiring bunny ninja needs a home with rabbit experience who will enjoy her bunitude. Goji loves her hay, pellets, treats and fresh veggies. She has good litter box habits. Goji likes to be pet on the head. She's not shy about expressing her opinions and is lightning fast. She does not care for other bunnies or for the cat in her foster home and would be best in a home where she can rule the house. She is a large rabbit, so would also appreciate lots of space in her new home. Currently fostering in the Raleigh-Durham area.

animals.Name: Ruby
animals.Description: Meet Ruby! She is very curious and loves to explore. Checking out all the fun things in the play space is one of her favorite activities. She is friendly with people and loves to be pet. She is a bit of a designer and can be picky about her personal space. Ruby will supervise carefully for any cleaning or redecorating. She also doesn't care to share any food - humans need to get their own snack! She wants to be the center of attention and does not care for cats (and probably not dogs either). She is about two years old, spayed, vaccinated, and ready for a family of her own. Currently fostering in the Raleigh-Durham, NC area.

animals.Name: Figgy Pudding
animals.Description: Figgy is a sweet, calm, big bunny who loves attention. Her favorite thing is for people to pet her. During snuggle time she will lay down and take it all in. She is very curious and enjoys exploring and munching on hay. Figgy loves treats, and mooching a few extra ones is one of her super powers. After exploring Figgy will flop out on the floor and enjoy some relaxation. She is about five years old and has very neat habits. She is spayed, vaccinated for RHDV2, and currently fostering in the Wilmington area.

animals.Name: Sally
animals.Description: Meet Sally! She is a spunky, fun girl who loves jumping and running around to explore. She is a bit shy at first, but loves a good head rub once she gets to know you. She enjoys her salads, especially if they have cilantro and parsley (a little carrot thrown in never hurts!). Sally loves fruit treats and blueberries, strawberries, and bananas are favorites. She is spayed, vaccinated for RHDV2, and ready for a home of her own. Sally is about two years old and is currently fostering in the Raleigh-Durham area.

animals.Name: Holly
animals.Description: Holly came to rescue with her eight tiny babies in December 2022. Now her little ones are teenagers and Holly is ready for a home of her own. She LOVES pets and is not shy about demanding people's attention. She enjoys going on adventures and likes to have lots of room to explore (bunny proofing is a must, as she also likes to climb). She does not like being enclosed and is happiest when she gets lots of exercise time. She is good with gentle children. She does not like her cat roommate and doesn't seem to like other rabbits, so would be best as a single bunny. Holly is about two years old, spayed, vaccinated for RHDV2, and is currently fostering in the Raleigh-Durham area.

animals.Name: Dancer
animals.Description: Meet Dancer! She is about six months old and very curious about everything. She is a bit nervous with people, but does like the occasional pet on her head. She is curious about the cat and gentle dog in her foster home and will sniff them through the gate. She loves running around, exploring, and chewing everything. Dancer enjoys hanging out in her hidey houses when it's time to relax. She has a great appetite and will try anything, but romaine, basil and cilantro are favorites. She is also an escape artist and has jumped a lower 24-inch x-pen so a taller enclosure would be best for her. She is spayed, vaccinated, and ready for a home of her own. Currently fostering in the Raleigh-Durham area.

animals.Name: Prancer
animals.Description: Say hello to Prancer! She is very outgoing and will let you pet her. She tolerates being picked up and will wiggle to get down. Prancer loves romaine lettuce, but doesn't have an adventurous palate and isn't very excited about new greens. She is a great hay eater, though. She loves running around and exploring, and is not destructive while out of her x-pen. She does enjoy shredding fleece, though. She has lots of fun in her dig box and that is her favorite toy. She is very well litter box trained. Prancer does not care for other bunnies. She is about six months old, spayed, vaccinated, and ready for a home. Currently fostering in the Raleigh-Durham area.

animals.Name: Luigi (FKA Cupid)
animals.Description: Luigi is about five months old and ready for a home of his own. He is very friendly and outgoing and loves to be petted. His favorite salad green is romaine lettuce, and he loves chewing his willow sticks. Luigi also loves to climb, so extra bunny-proofing is a must in his new home. He is neutered and vaccinated for RHDV2. Luigi is currently fostering in the Raleigh-Durham area.

animals.Name: Comet
animals.Description: Comet is the first of Holly's babies to be ready for a home of his own. He is a curious bunny who loves to search for his greens up high, buried in hay, or stuffed in a paper towel tube. Little reindeer bunnies love to forage, and exploring is one of his favorite activities. He is playful and has lots of fun running zoomies and dancing with binkies. He also enjoys playing with his toss toys, including his favorite pinecone. Comet is social and approaches people easily. After exploring, he sits or lays on the couch or floor near near his foster family when watching TV. He loves head and face rubs. Comet is great with his litter box and has not had accidents when free roaming. He is comfortable with gentle dogs. Comet is eight months old and neutered. He is currently fostering in the Raleigh-Durham area.

animals.Name: Vixen
animals.Description: Meet Vixen. She's one of our reindeer babies that was born in December 2022. Vixen is about seven months old and has lots of young bunny energy. She loves to run and play! Exploring is one of her favorite activities. She will tolerate petting, but is too busy running around to sit still for long. A home with lots of space would be perfect! She loves to chew so bunny proofing will be important in her new home. She does seem interested in the other bunnies in her foster home, so she might enjoy having a friend in the future. Vixen is spayed, vaccinated, and ready for a home of her own. Currently fostering in the Raleigh-Durham area.

animals.Name: Mario (FKA Donner)
animals.Description: Meet Mario! He's about five months old, neutered, and ready for a home of his own. He has beautiful dark brown/gray fur! Mario loves to play with his toss toys and willow sticks are some of his favorite things. He is shy when meeting new people, but warms up once he gets to know you. He enjoys his timothy hay and is always ready for snacks! He is vaccinated for RHDV2. Mario is fostering in the Raleigh-Durham, NC area.

animals.Name: Blitzen
animals.Description: Meet Blitzen! He is one of Holly's babies and he's ready for his forever home. Blitzen is a very happy bunny who loves to do double and triple binkies - he will even binky off the wall! He is very curious and loves to know what is behind every door. Exploring is one of his favorite activities. He is good with nice cats and gentle dogs. Blitzen does great with eating his hay, greens, and pellets and has not met a treat he didn't like. His foster family says he is a sweet little guy. He is neutered, vaccinated for RHDV2, and ready to go home. He is currently fostering in the Raleigh-Durham area.

animals.Name: Dasher
animals.Description: Dasher is one of Holly's babies and is ready for a home to call her own. She is very shy and takes time to warm up to people and places. She seems to gain confidence from being near other bunnies and may benefit from having a friend. She's not really into pets, but does enjoy quietly exploring and decorating her cardboard houses. She would be best in a quiet home where she can feel settled and enjoy some bunny zen. She is about seven months old, spayed, and vaccinated for RHDV2. Currently fostering in the Raleigh-Durham, NC area.

animals.Name: Benji
animals.Description: Benji is a sweet, lovable bunny. He is playful once he has warmed up to his environment. His foster family adores the way he greets them when it's breakfast/dinner time and how he dances across the carpet. He loves to hop up on people when they lay on the floor with him. Benji is very good at using his litter box. He's not a big chewer and leaves alone most things he shouldn't be nibbling, though he does have a taste for shoes. He has proven wonderful with kids in his foster home and would be an amazing addition to any family. Benji is about 1.5 years old, neutered, and vaccinated for RHDV2. He is currently fostering in the Wilmington, NC area.

animals.Name: Sacha
animals.Description: Sasha is a model house rabbit - she is happy to help make the bed, fluff the pillows, and clean the furniture (if licking it counts)! She loves digging in blankets and pillows, but is careful not to chew or tear them up. She has perfect litter box habits and is very food and treat motivated. She is lower to medium energy level and will offer some small zoomies and binkies, but usually very happy to lounge around. She is more on the independent side but is very curious and will hop up and honk at humans when they come into her room. She's very talkative! She likes being pet, but is not a snuggle bun and needs a human who can respect her space. So far her favorite toy other than blankets has been plain brown packing paper. She also loves having a stuffed animal in her pen and grooms it often. She may be interested in a friend, or may only prefer stuffed animal friends that follow her rules. Sasha is about six years old, spayed, and vaccinated. She is fostering in the Raleigh-Durham area.

animals.Name: Winnie (Winnifred)
animals.Description: Meet the dynamic duo Winnie and Sandy! Winnie enjoys pets and tolerates being held as long as treats are involved, but she prefers to lay back and do her own thing. Sandy will tolerate pets but will demand food at the same time. She will jump on your lap for treats and attention, so get ready! Both are very food motivated and will come running when called or when the food bag/jar opens. They are both curious buns who love to explore and prefer to be in a home that offers free roaming options. This is when they show off their real skills with their binkies and zooming. They are working on their improving their litter training, and do better in a bigger space with multiple litter boxes. They love chewing on cardboard and exploring tunnels and hidey spaces. Both Winnie and Sandy are spayed, vaccinated for RHDV2, and ready to find their forever home! They are currently being fostered in the Raleigh-Durham area.

animals.Name: Sandy (Sandstorm)
animals.Description: Meet the dynamic duo Winnie and Sandy! Winnie enjoys pets and tolerates being held as long as treats are involved, but she prefers to lay back and do her own thing. Sandy will tolerate pets but will demand food at the same time. She will jump on your lap for treats and attention, so get ready! Both are very food motivated and will come running when called or when the food bag/jar opens. They are both curious buns who love to explore and prefer to be in a home that offers free roaming options. This is when they show off their real skills with their binkies and zooming. They are working on their improving their litter training, and do better in a bigger space with multiple litter boxes. They love chewing on cardboard and exploring tunnels and hidey spaces. Both Winnie and Sandy are spayed, vaccinated for RHDV2, and ready to find their forever home!  in the Raleigh-Durham area.

animals.Name: Petra
animals.Description:
Meet Petra and Bijou! Petra is a sweet girl, but still kind of shy. She readily accepts pets, and especially loves to "purr" while having her head and neck stroked. She's a whiz with food puzzles, and she especially loves puzzles with her stacking cups. She loves to rearrange things in her space, and will regularly go and redecorate after cleaning. She's not too much of an explorer! She's pretty content to sit on something soft and chill out most of the time. Her favorite treats are dried strawberries and fresh blueberries;
she eats most greens and veggies, but her favorites are spinach, arugula, and carrots. Bijou is a little explorer! She loves to investigate new things and spaces in her room, and just recently she's learned about jumping up on the bed and hanging out there! She is still learning to accept pets from humans, but has made a lot of progress; she's much more high-energy and playful than her mom Petra. She loves to chew, so plenty of toys are a must for this girl. Bijou prefers hay and pellets over greens. Her favorite treat is dried strawberries. Both bunnies are spayed and vaccinated and ready for a home of their own. Currently fostering in the Raleigh-Durham, NC area.

animals.Name: Bijou
animals.Description:
Meet Petra and Bijou! Petra is a sweet girl, but still kind of shy. She readily accepts pets, and especially loves to "purr" while having her head and neck stroked. She's a whiz with food puzzles, and she especially loves puzzles with her stacking cups. She loves to rearrange things in her space, and will regularly go and redecorate after cleaning. She's not too much of an explorer! She's pretty content to sit on something soft and chill out most of the time. Her favorite treats are dried strawberries and fresh blueberries;
she eats most greens and veggies, but her favorites are spinach, arugula, and carrots. Bijou is a little explorer! She loves to investigate new things and spaces in her room, and just recently she's learned about jumping up on the bed and hanging out there! She is still learning to accept pets from humans, but has made a lot of progress; she's much more high-energy and playful than her mom Petra. She loves to chew, so plenty of toys are a must for this girl. Bijou prefers hay and pellets over greens. Her favorite treat is dried strawberries. Both bunnies are spayed and vaccinated and ready for a home of their own. Currently fostering in the Raleigh-Durham, NC area.

animals.Name: Dug
animals.Description: Say hello to Dug. This sweet guy is named after the fun-loving character and loves to come say "hi".  He's very outgoing and loves exploring his space (and your space, and possibly your neighbor's space). He loves to jump, so a tall enclosure or an enclosure with a roof would be best for him. He enjoys attention and is not shy about climbing on laps for pets. He was good with the cat in his foster home. Chew toys are his favorites, so plenty of those please! Dug is about two years old, neutered, and vaccinated for RHDV2. He's ready for his next adventure! Currently fostering in the Raleigh-Durham, NC area.

animals.Name: Lebowski
animals.Description: Meet Lebowski! He's had a rough start in his life. He came from a very unfortunate situation, being dumped on the streets. Initially he didn't even know how to be a bunny. He has bloomed in foster care! He has learned how to binky, tooth chatter and to beg for food. He's full of personality and love. His favorite past time is playing with his chew and toss toys. Lebowski is very good with his liter habits and there's not a veggie or fruit he will turn down. He is about two years old, neutered, vaccinated, and ready for a family to love. Currently fostering in the Wilmington, NC area.

animals.Name: Mumford
animals.Description: Meet Mumford. Mumford is a tidy and well-behaved bun who is very shy around humans. He is slowly opening up and showing off his binkies for his foster mom, and we think that another bunny friend would help him gain confidence and come out of his shell. Mumford seems interested in other rabbits, but can be reactive and needs a calmer friend. Mumford enjoys having tunnels and boxes to nap in and likes to play hide and seek in the curtains in his foster room. He is great while free-roaming and displays no destructive tendencies in his foster home. He is very timid and shy fellow, and is looking for a family with lots of love, patience, and treats to build trust. He doesn't eat much salad, but loves Science Selective loops and dried strawberry. Mumford is estimated to be 1-2 years old, neutered, vaccinated and ready for a family. Currently fostering in the Raleigh-Durham, NC area.

animals.Name: Triscuit
animals.Description: Meet Triscuit! This big girl has a strong, in charge personality. She loves being petted and isn't afraid to let humans know they cannot stop! She loves running up and down the hallway and entertains her foster family with her antics. Hay is her kryptonite and one of her favorite things to eat. Triscuit is a large bunny and will need an extra large enclosure in her new home. She would love a rabbit-savvy family that will enjoy her feisty personality. Triscuit is about 1.5 years old, spayed and vaccinated. She is currently fostering in the Wilmington, NC area.

animals.Name: Cinnamon
animals.Description: Meet Cinnamon!  Cinnamon is a gentle, doe-eyed girl. She enjoys pets and occasionally asks for snuggles once comfortable in her environment.  She loves to play with stacking cups, dig boxes, food logic puzzles, and playing in her dig box.  She prefers to keep her living area neat, which means she is great with her litter box.  She loves to check out what's happening around the house but enjoys relaxing in her space.  She loves her salad, hay, and treats!  Cinnamon is spayed, vaccinated, and ready for her own home. Currently fostering in the Raleigh-Durham, NC area.

animals.Name: Juniper
animals.Description: Meet Juniper!  Juniper is five months old and a laid-back bunny.  She enjoys pets and cuddles once comfortable in her environment. She loves to play with stacking cups, dig boxes, food logic puzzles, and playing in her dig box. She loves to check out what's happening around the house but enjoys relaxing in her space. She is a foodie!  She loves hay, some salad, and treats. Juniper is spayed, vaccinated, and ready for her own home. Currently fostering in the Raleigh-Durham, NC area.

animals.Name: Wiggles
animals.Description: Introducing the adventurous escape artist, Wiggles!  Wiggles is five months old and an explorer at heart.  She enjoys pets and snuggles once comfortable in her environment. She loves to play with stacking cups, dig boxes, food logic puzzles, and playing in her dig box. She loves to check out what's happening around the house but enjoys relaxing in her space. She loves her salad, hay, and treats! Wiggles is spayed, vaccinated, and ready for her own home. Currently fostering in the Raleigh-Durham, NC area.

animals.Name: Wednesday
animals.Description: Say hello to Wednesday! This lady is a bit of a neat freak with great housekeeping skills. She keeps a tidy space and has good litter habits. Wednesday loves any and all toys you give her. She also enjoys begging for treats (her favorites are broccoli, basil, dill, and banana chips). Once she gets to know you she will ask for nose pets and will fall asleep if you stroke her nose to her ears for long enough. She's very smart and super playful and likes to show off her acrobatic skills with lots of binkies - she LOVES to free roam. After playtime she enjoys relaxing on the couch. She has done well in a home with adults and gentle children, however she does easily startle and is very shy with strangers at first so may be best in a quieter home. She is estimated to be 2-3 years old, and is spayed, vaccinated, and ready for her forever home. She is currently fostering in the Raleigh-Durham, NC area.

animals.Name: Callie
animals.Description: Meet Callie. She's a super well-behaved bun. She is excellent with her litter box and likes a tidy space. She is shy and quite easily startled by unexpected noises or fast movements so would be best in a quiet home. She enjoys company and will tend to loaf nearby on the carpet when her foster family is working, but prefers to be petted at her own pace. She likes the space to free roam very much, and expresses her appreciation with zoomies. She doesn't seem to be a picky eater and always clears her plates of greens: dandelion greens, red leaf lettuce, and green leaf lettuce are favorites. She is also a big fan of apple treats. For toys/enrichment, she absolutely loves willow baskets, palm bowls, and apple sticks. She also had lots of fun with a toy box stuffed with orchard hay. She loves simple cardboard boxes, preferring her hidey houses to be sturdy. She is about 1.5 years old, spayed, vaccinated, and ready for a home of her own. Currently fostering in the Raleigh-Durham, NC area.

animals.Name: Pumpkin
animals.Description: Meet Pumpkin and Spice! Pumpkin came to rescue in fall 2023 after having her babies in a local shelter. She was able to raise her little ones safely in foster care. Baby Spice decided to stick with mom Pumpkin, so they are being adopted together. These girls are  playful, curious, sweet, and a little bit mischievous. Spice likes getting occasional pets and is into exploring new rooms and toys. They both like to jump and climb on things. They don't really like to be held, but are happy to return to their enclosure at mealtime or for treats. They both love their pellets and hay. Pumpkin is about 1.5 years old and Spice is about 6 months old. They are spayed, vaccinated, and ready for a home of their own. Currently fostering in the Raleigh-Durham area.

animals.Name: Toffee
animals.Description: Toffee is another one of Pumpkin's babies, rescued in October 2023. He is a love bug and enjoys lots of attention from people - bring on the pets! He enjoys spending time with his foster family. He is a young bunny with lots of energy, so he would love a home with plenty of space to run and play. He loves to get his zoomies out! Toffee sports a fancy hairdo and will need regular grooming to stay looking his best. He enjoys his timothy hay and all kinds of veggies and fruits - no picky eaters here! Toffee is about 8 months old, neutered, vaccinated for RHDV2, and ready for a home to call his own. Currently fostering in the Raleigh-Durham, NC area.

animals.Name: Spice
animals.Description: Meet Pumpkin and Spice! Pumpkin came to rescue in fall 2023 after having her babies in a local shelter. She was able to raise her little ones safely in foster care. Baby Spice decided to stick with mom Pumpkin, so they are being adopted together. These girls are  playful, curious, sweet, and a little bit mischievous. Spice likes getting occasional pets and is into exploring new rooms and toys. They both like to jump and climb on things. They don't really like to be held, but are happy to return to their enclosure at mealtime or for treats. They both love their pellets and hay. Pumpkin is about 1.5 years old and Spice is about 6 months old. They are spayed, vaccinated, and ready for a home of their own. Currently fostering in the Raleigh-Durham area.

animals.Name: Maple
animals.Description: Maple is a very sweet bunny. He likes exploring the house when he first gets out of his pen and then he will settle down for a rest. He's quite clean and often grooms his fabulous hair. He will need frequent grooming to keep his beautiful coat in good condition. He likes to visit his foster mom while they watch TV and nudge for attention. He also likes to jump up on the couch - climbing is fun! He will climb on tables and shelves to see what is up there so beware! Bunny proofing beyond the floor is a must for this fellow. His favorite treats are apple, banana chips, and carrot. He eats lots of hay and enjoys all his salads. For toys he loves cardboard toys, paper, and palm leaf plates. He has good litter box habits. He is neutered, vaccinated, and ready for home of his own. Currently fostering in the Raleigh-Durham area.

animals.Name: Spirit
animals.Description: Meet Snickers and Spirit. These little guys are two of Pumpkin's babies and came to rescue a few days after being born. They are about six months old and best friends. Snickers is very chill overall, but does sometimes startle (usually because his brother is full of drama). He loves to run and play but is not very adventurous with his exploring. He will tolerate pets and grooming (grooming is a must with his long fur!). He is still a little suspicious of greens and new foods but will eventually try them. Spirit startles easily but is very curious and likes to investigate visitors and situations. He is very adventurous and loves to get into trouble chewing and digging. Like his brother, he is skeptical of new foods and treats. He loves toys and can bunstruct toys in a single day. He likes gentle pets once he gets to know you. Both boys are great with their litter habits. They would be best in a home with adults or older children and are ok with cats. They are neutered, vaccinated, and ready for a home. Currently fostering in the Raleigh-Durham area.

animals.Name: Snickers
animals.Description: Meet Snickers and Spirit. These little guys are two of Pumpkin's babies and came to rescue a few days after being born. They are about six months old and best friends. Snickers is very chill overall, but does sometimes startle (usually because his brother is full of drama). He loves to run and play but is not very adventurous with his exploring. He will tolerate pets and grooming (grooming is a must with his long fur!). He is still a little suspicious of greens and new foods but will eventually try them. Spirit startles easily but is very curious and likes to investigate visitors and situations. He is very adventurous and loves to get into trouble chewing and digging. Like his brother, he is skeptical of new foods and treats. He loves toys and can bunstruct toys in a single day. He likes gentle pets once he gets to know you. Both boys are great with their litter habits. They would be best in a home with adults or older children and are ok with cats. They are neutered, vaccinated, and ready for a home. Currently fostering in the Raleigh-Durham area.

animals.Name: Ember
animals.Description: Meet Ember. She is one of Pumpkin's babies and is very laid back. She is great with her litter box and enjoys free roaming. She loves exploring her surroundings and checking everything out. Ember is good with cats and gentle dogs and may even enjoy a bunny friend for company. She will need frequent grooming to keep her beautiful fur in top shape. She isn't a big fan of her spa days but will tolerate brushing and nail trims. She enjoys romaine lettuce, basil, cilantro, and dill in her salads, but is not a big fan of fruit. Her favorite toys are her bunny box hanging toys and palm bowls. She has been a joy to her foster family and will be a wonderful companion. She is about six months old, spayed, vaccinated, and ready for a home of her own. Currently fostering in the Raleigh-Durham area.

animals.Name: Casper
animals.Description: Meet Casper! He's one of Pumpkin's babies, rescued in October 2023. He is a young, fun loving bunny who craves interaction and attention - plenty of pets please! He has the softest white fur and beautiful blue eyes. He is an avid eater of timothy hay and expects his afternoon treats on time! Humans better not be late! He also loves his veggies and fruits. He runs laps around his pen in the morning for his pellet breakfast time because he is so excited. Casper's foster family thinks he is a treasure and a wonderful companion! He is neutered, vaccinated for RHDV2 and ready for a home of his own. Currently fostering in the Raleigh-Durham, NC area.

animals.Name: Gavin
animals.Description: Gavin is a young, friendly fellow who is looking for a home where he has lots of time to run around and hang out with the family.  It's hard to say which he loves more - exploring every inch of his space or following his people around, making sure he doesn't miss any of the action.  If you aren't paying enough attention to him he will jump in your lap and demand it.  He will literally follow you around the house, and would probably love to help you do the dishes or sweep the floors if you could teach him how.  Gavin is about 5 pounds, neutered and litterbox trained with a voracious appetite and a zest for life that has to be admired.

animals.Name: Piper
animals.Description: Meet Piper. She is about 1 year old, spayed and vaccinated. She has a beautiful silky solid black coat. Piper is very outgoing and a ball of energy. She loves head rubs and back rubs when you can get a snuggle in. She tolerates being picked up but will wiggle to get down. She loves romaine lettuce and her favorite treats are carrots, strawberries and cantaloupe. She is a great hay eater. She loves running around and exploring, and isn't scared to check out new areas. Piper is litter training very well. She enjoys digging in her litter/dig boxes. She is also a great bowl flipper! She does well with other bunnies and gentle dogs. Piper is ready for her forever home. Currently fostering in Wilmington, NC.

animals.Name: Jelly Bean
animals.Description: Miss Jellybean is a sweet, curious, ball of love! She equally enjoys a good exploratory hop and pets and snuggles. Need a tv or movie buddy? She's your gal, especially if you'll pet her-she'll snuggle right in! Doing some housework? She's a great supervisor, keeping you on task and motivating you by presenting for pets. She's got perfect litter box habits and loves hay and salad of all kinds. She doesn't mind being picked up and will tell you if she's not into it. She also enjoys sitting on the occasional lap. She is spayed, vaccinated, and ready for a home. Currently fostering in the Raleigh-Durham area.

animals.Name: Gumdrop
animals.Description: Meet Gumdrop. Anyone following Triangle Rabbits' social media is already familiar with this little lady, found over the winter living in a drainpipe in a Wilmington park. She has been thriving in foster care, enjoying her toys, lots of attention from her foster parents and getting all kinds of exercise where she loves to show off her acrobatic and dance skills. She is currently around 6 months old, spayed, excellent with her litter box, and ready for her forever family. She loves people and, once she feels comfortable with them, will follow them around the house begging for attention. She has been vaccinated for RHDV2 and is currently fostering in the Wilmington, NC area.

animals.Name: Cookies
animals.Description: Meet Cookies! This little guy had a rough start. He was found stray, hopping by the side of the road, and was picked up in a dog's mouth. He also had a lot of fur missing from his feet and tail, possibly from urine burns from a rarely cleaned living space. Cookies has done a lot of healing since coming to rescue in March. He's grown back his fur and now this adolescent rabbit loves to run about his foster home at top speed or hop all over, including onto chairs. He loves showing off his binky and racing skills! He's been known to climb furniture and unplug things while chewing on the cord protector (so bunny proofing for the marauding rabbit is a must!). He is getting more comfortable with being pet but doesn't like to snuggle - he has things to do! He is very food motivated, so it's easy to get him in his pen with pellets or salad instead of lifting him. He will gladly hop into his carrier, but expects yummy food there! He is an entertaining and bossy bunny, making his foster family laugh at salad time by snatching his favorite pieces. Picture a tiny rabbit bounding away, head and tail held high, with a piece of kale so big he can barely hold it off the ground! He does still tend to nip stray things like seams in jeans and an errant human standing where he needs to run. He would like a home with lots of bunny proofed room to roam and humans who love him and appreciate his spunk. He is neutered and vaccinated. Currently fostering in the Raleigh-Durham area.

animals.Name: Logan
animals.Description: Logan is a sweet outgoing bunny that just wants to be loved, and he will let you know! He is very vocal and will grunt until you start petting him! He also doesn't mind being picked up for cuddles. Logan loves to explore and would enjoy hopping around a bunny safe home, without a worry for accidents as he is litter trained. He will also need to be groomed regularly to keep his beautiful fur in good condition. Logan is neutered, vaccinated, and ready for a home of his own. Currently fostering in the Raleigh-Durham area.

animals.Name: Cocoa
animals.Description: Meet Cocoa. She is about 1.5 years old, spayed, vaccinated, and ready for a home. She loves to play with her toys, including stacking cups, cardboard rolls, willow balls, and straw hats (hats are the best!). She's into parkour and can jump her ex-pen when she's motivated enough, so an enclosure with a top would be best. After her workout, she likes to do a spot of remodeling in her cardboard boxes and grass tunnels to go for the shredded look. Cocoa is into health food and enjoys cilantro, parsley, romaine, and kale in her salads. She prefers to graze on her pellets and hay. She's very friendly and likes attention, following her foster family around the living room and then jumping up on the couch for pats. She's a little wary of strangers, but once she gets to know them she's ready for treats. Cocoa is great with her litter box and does great during her play time. If you're looking for an active bun who likes to snuggle she might be your perfect match! Currently fostering in the Raleigh-Durham area.

animals.Name: Strudel
animals.Description: Say hello to Strudel! This beautiful girl loves hanging out with her foster family, though she doesn't always like to be pet. She LOVES to run and will do lots of zoomies and binkies all over the room - then she is ready for her nap! She enjoys snoozing on her bed during the day and her favorite way to sleep is completely flopped over. Her favorite chew toys are carpet and baseboards - bunny proofing is a must for this bun! She is super clean with her litter box. She loves treats, but doesn't respond to sounds like the treat jar or people walking around so she may be hard of hearing. She will need a family who doesn't mind giving visual cues so she doesn't get startled. She loves cilantro and leaf lettuce and meadow loops are a favorite treat - she will come running. This sweet girl is spayed, vaccinated, and ready for a home of her own. Currently fostering in the Raleigh-Durham, NC area.

animals.Name: Wafer
animals.Description: Meet Wafer!  This 6 pound mini lop is a bundle of energy.  She is a very determined girl and usually figures out a way to get where she wants to go, whether it's escaping from her enclosure or jumping on high tables to get a better view.  Because of this, she would be best as a free roam bunny, with lots of time to spend with her human.  She is a very friendly rabbit who loves hanging out with people as long as they are paying attention to her every demand.  If you want a bunny best buddy, Wafer is for you.  Wafer is spayed, vaccinated and fostering in Wilmington, NC.

animals.Name: Remy
animals.Description: Hi! I'm Remy. I am a spunky lionhead mix with a big personality. I love to explore and I don't scare easily. I'm even okay with the vacuum! I love sniffing my foster humans but I'm not a fan of snuggles or being picked up. However, I'll let you pet me while I eat my pellets in the morning and my salad at dinner. A few of my favorites are lavender, basil, sage, and yarrow! I know my schedule well! My human thinks I'm pretty smart and catch on to things quickly. I'm always trying to run out my door to explore and find something to chew on. For that reason, if I'm free roam the room will need to be bunny-proofed. I keep a tidy home and keep myself looking my best. I am my happiest when I have the space to run! I am spayed and vaccinated. Currently fostering in the Raleigh, Durham area.
